title: China’s Geely Plans Bid for Malaysian Car Maker Proton - WSJ
text:
Asian Business News China’s Geely Plans Bid for Malaysian Car Maker Proton Investment by owner of Volvo cars would add to growing China-Malaysia ties; France’s PSA Group submitted bid Tuesday By Yantoultra Ngui in Kuala Lumpur, Yantoultra Ngui Trefor Moss in Shanghai and Trefor Moss Kane Wu in Hong Kong Kane Wu Feb. 21, 2017 7:02 a.m. ET 
China may soon cinch another knot in its business ties with Malaysia. 
Zhejiang Geely Holding Group Co., the Chinese auto maker that owns Volvo Cars, is readying a bid for a majority stake in Malaysian car maker Proton Holdings Bhd., according to people familiar with the situation. France’s PSA Group, which makes Peugeot and Citroën cars, said Tuesday that it has submitted a bid.
